<B>Steps to duplicate:</B><BR>
<INPUT TYPE="hidden"  NAME="steps" VAlUE="If I get disconnected while my character is running, it continues to run at full speed until the server determines that the connection has been broken.<p>Once the server suspects that a connection will be lost it should store the character's position. (first instance of a yellow link.)  If the connection is actually lost, it should restore that saved position.<p>This will hopefully make it easier to locate bodies in the case of lag death or at least keep the player in the general location at the time the connection is lost.<p>I'd also suggest that between the yellow link and disconnect that the player should not be allowed to die.  If the player does die, his state is restored to the point when he first entered the yellow link.">
If I get disconnected while my character is running, it continues to run at full speed until the server determines that the connection has been broken.<p>Once the server suspects that a connection will be lost it should store the character's position. (first instance of a yellow link.)  If the connection is actually lost, it should restore that saved position.<p>This will hopefully make it easier to locate bodies in the case of lag death or at least keep the player in the general location at the time the connection is lost.<p>I'd also suggest that between the yellow link and disconnect that the player should not be allowed to die.  If the player does die, his state is restored to the point when he first entered the yellow link.
